Duties and Responsibilities
 Monitor inventory levels and liaise with site operations for material orders
 Assist in employee PPE request (MF)
 Maintain and ensure all inventory movements/adjustments are promptly recorded in the system
 Conduct regular stock take of inventory
 Reconcile system records with physical stock count
 Prepare inventory reports for management review
 Timekeeping for workers deployed at workshop
 Undertake any other ad-hoc duties assigned by the Immediate supervisor

Qualifications / Requirements
 Candidate must possess at least Professional Certificate/NITEC, Diploma/Advanced/Higher/Graduate Diploma in Engineering (Inventory/Materials Management) or equivalent
 At least 2 Year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this position
 Preferably with experience in a Petrochemical and/or Marine industry
 Familiarity with Marine/Oil &amp; Gas/Petrochemical rules, regulations, best practices and performance standards preferred
 Proficient in MS Office application specifically PowerPoint, Word and Excel
 Possess effective communication skills
 Able to work in a team or independently
 Preferably staying in the west area
 5.5-day work week